# dataset-scout configuration
#
# Copy to `.env` (which is git-ignored) and fill in. The CLI auto-loads
# this file from the current working directory at startup. Library
# callers can also pass values via ScoutContext directly.

# ─── Universal LLM model id (recommended) ───────────────────────────
# Set this to any litellm-style model id. dataset-scout dispatches
# based on the prefix; litellm handles the per-provider auth flow.
#
#   github_copilot/<model>   Uses your existing GitHub Copilot
#                            subscription. On first use, litellm runs
#                            an OAuth device-code flow (you paste a
#                            code into github.com/login/device) and
#                            caches the token at
#                            ~/.config/litellm/github_copilot/.
#                            No env var needed.
#                            CAVEAT: GitHub's Copilot terms of service
#                            scope it to "code suggestions in editor
#                            and similar." Using it for non-coding
#                            agentic workflows is a gray area; you
#                            assume the policy risk.
#
#   github/<model>           Free GitHub Models tier. Reads GITHUB_TOKEN
#                            (a fine-grained PAT with `models:read`).
#                            Tighter rate limits than Copilot.
#
#   openai/<model>           Reads OPENAI_API_KEY.
#   anthropic/<model>        Reads ANTHROPIC_API_KEY.
#   azure/<deployment>       Same as setting the AZURE_OPENAI_* vars
#                            below; uses Entra (no API key).
#
# Examples:
#   DATASET_SCOUT_MODEL=github_copilot/gpt-5-mini
#   DATASET_SCOUT_MODEL=github_copilot/claude-sonnet-4-5
#   DATASET_SCOUT_MODEL=github/gpt-4o-mini
#   DATASET_SCOUT_MODEL=openai/gpt-4o
# DATASET_SCOUT_MODEL=

# Optional: GitHub Copilot device-code flow caches its token here by
# default. Override if you want a different location (or to share a
# pre-authenticated cache across machines).
# GITHUB_COPILOT_TOKEN_DIR=

# Optional: GitHub Models PAT (only needed for the `github/<model>`
# route, not `github_copilot/`). Create at
# https://github.com/settings/personal-access-tokens with
# `models:read` permission.
# GITHUB_TOKEN=

# ─── Azure OpenAI (legacy / Entra auth) ─────────────────────────────
# This is the original auth path. Either set DATASET_SCOUT_MODEL above
# OR these AZURE_OPENAI_* vars; if both are set, DATASET_SCOUT_MODEL
# wins. Auth is Entra (no API key): run `az login` once and the
# DefaultAzureCredential chain handles the rest. In CI / Azure-hosted
# environments, managed identity or a service-principal env-var trio
# (AZURE_TENANT_ID / AZURE_CLIENT_ID / AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET) work too.

# AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT=https://your-aoai-resource.openai.azure.com/
# AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT=gpt-4o-mini
# Optional: pin an API version. Default tracks a stable GA release.
# AZURE_OPENAI_API_VERSION=2024-10-21
# Optional embeddings deployment for the embedding-fit pipeline stage
# (only consulted when DATASET_SCOUT_EMBEDDING_BACKEND=aoai).
# AZURE_OPENAI_EMBEDDING_DEPLOYMENT=text-embedding-3-small

# ─── Embeddings (label_intent_fit pipeline stage) ───────────────────
# Picks which backend computes the dense embeddings used by the
# embedding-fit stage. Independent of DATASET_SCOUT_MODEL — chat and
# embeddings can use different providers.
#
#   sbert  (default) Local CPU sentence-transformers. Requires the
#                    optional extra: `pip install dataset-scout[local-
#                    embeddings]`. ~80MB model, runs on CPU. No
#                    network. When the extra isn't installed, the
#                    stage no-ops gracefully.
#   aoai             Azure OpenAI embeddings via
#                    AZURE_OPENAI_EMBEDDING_DEPLOYMENT (above). Same
#                    Entra auth as the chat path.
#   none             Skip the embedding-fit stage entirely.
# DATASET_SCOUT_EMBEDDING_BACKEND=sbert
#
# Optional: override the model name for the chosen backend. For sbert
# this is an HF repo id; default is "sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-
# L6-v2" (384-dim, fast). Try "BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5" for stronger
# semantic match at the cost of a slightly larger download.
# DATASET_SCOUT_EMBEDDING_MODEL=

# ─── HuggingFace (M1a) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Public datasets are accessible without a token, but rate limits are
# friendlier with one. https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens
HUGGINGFACE_HUB_TOKEN=
# HF_TOKEN is honored as an alias.
# HF_TOKEN=

# ─── Kaggle (M1b) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required only if Kaggle source is enabled.
# KAGGLE_USERNAME=
# KAGGLE_KEY=

# ─── dataset-scout knobs ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Override default paths.
# DATASET_SCOUT_CACHE_DIR=
# DATASET_SCOUT_CONFIG_DIR=
# DATASET_SCOUT_OUT_DIR=
